<subSubSection pageId="1" pageNumber="94" type="distribution">
<paragraph pageId="1" pageNumber="94">Distribution.</paragraph>
<paragraph pageId="1" pageNumber="94">
Hawaiian Islands, northern 
<normalizedToken originalValue="Kaua‘i">Kaua'i</normalizedToken>
, known only from the Hanalei District, growing along streams or on windward upper valley slopes and summit areas above the valleys at c. 740-1280 m (Fig. 
<figureCitation captionStart="Figure 3" captionStartId="F3" captionText="Figure 3. Distribution map showing known locations of Perrottetia wichmaniorum on Kaua'i." figureDoi="10.3897/phytokeys.115.30657.figure3" httpUri="https://binary.pensoft.net/fig/260626" pageId="1" pageNumber="94">3</figureCitation>
). Collections are known from the upper Waioli Valley in the east and along the 
<normalizedToken originalValue="Nā">Na</normalizedToken>
Pali Coast to 
<normalizedToken originalValue="Awa‘awapuhi">Awa'awapuhi</normalizedToken>
Valley in the west, although they likely also occur in intervening areas with suitable habitat.
</paragraph>
