<subSubSection pageId="2" pageNumber="95" type="habitat">
<paragraph pageId="2" pageNumber="95">
<pageBreakToken pageId="2" pageNumber="95" start="start">Habitat</pageBreakToken>
and ecology.
</paragraph>
<paragraph pageId="2" pageNumber="95">
This new species grows in diverse wet forest with species of 
<taxonomicName class="Magnoliopsida" family="Myrtaceae" genus="Metrosideros" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Plantae" lsidName="Metrosideros" order="Myrtales" pageId="2" pageNumber="95" phylum="Magnoliophyta" rank="genus">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="2" pageNumber="95">Metrosideros</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
Banks ex Gaertn. dominant, associated with species of 
<taxonomicName class="Magnoliopsida" family="Araliaceae" genus="Cheirodendron" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF,CoL" kingdom="Plantae" lsidName="Cheirodendron" order="Apiales" pageId="2" pageNumber="95" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="genus">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="2" pageNumber="95">Cheirodendron</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
Nutt. ex Seemann, 
<taxonomicName class="Dicotyledoneae" family="Myrtaceae" genus="Syzygium" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Plantae" lsidName="Syzygium" order="Myrtiflorae" pageId="2" pageNumber="95" phylum="Angiospermae" rank="genus">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="2" pageNumber="95">Syzygium</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
Gaertn., 
<taxonomicName class="Magnoliopsida" family="Rubiaceae" genus="Psychotria" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Plantae" lsidName="Psychotria" order="Gentianales" pageId="2" pageNumber="95" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="genus">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="2" pageNumber="95">Psychotria</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
L., 
<taxonomicName class="Dicotyledoneae" family="Rutaceae" genus="Melicope" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Plantae" lsidName="Melicope" order="Rutales" pageId="2" pageNumber="95" phylum="Angiospermae" rank="genus">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="2" pageNumber="95">Melicope</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
J. R. Forst. &amp; G. Forst., 
<taxonomicName class="Magnoliopsida" family="Hydrangeaceae" genus="Broussaisia" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Plantae" lsidName="Broussaisia" order="Cornales" pageId="2" pageNumber="95" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="genus">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="2" pageNumber="95">Broussaisia</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
Gaud., 
<taxonomicName class="Magnoliopsida" family="Asteraceae" genus="Dubautia" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF,CoL" kingdom="Plantae" lsidName="Dubautia" order="Asterales" pageId="2" pageNumber="95" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="genus">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="2" pageNumber="95">Dubautia</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
Gaud., 
<taxonomicName class="Monocotyledoneae" family="Liliaceae" genus="Smilax" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Plantae" lsidName="Smilax" order="Liliiflorae" pageId="2" pageNumber="95" phylum="Angiospermae" rank="genus">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="2" pageNumber="95">Smilax</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
Tourn. ex L., 
<taxonomicName class="Liliopsida" family="Asteliaceae" genus="Astelia" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF,CoL" kingdom="Plantae" lsidName="Astelia" order="Asparagales" pageId="2" pageNumber="95" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="genus">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="2" pageNumber="95">Astelia</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
Banks &amp; Sol. ex R. Br., and diverse ferns including 
<taxonomicName class="Filicopsida" family="Gleicheniaceae" genus="Dicranopteris" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Plantae" lsidName="Dicranopteris linearis" order="Gleicheniales" pageId="2" pageNumber="95" phylum="Pteridophyta" rank="species" species="linearis">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="2" pageNumber="95">Dicranopteris linearis</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
(Burm. f.) Underw., 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Kaulfuss" authorityYear="1820" class="Filicopsida" family="Dicksoniaceae" genus="Cibotium" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Plantae" lsidName="Cibotium" order="Polypodiales" pageId="2" pageNumber="95" phylum="Pteridophyta" rank="genus">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="2" pageNumber="95">Cibotium</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
Kaulf., 
<taxonomicName class="Polypodiopsida" family="Blechnaceae" genus="Sadleria" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF,CoL" kingdom="Plantae" lsidName="Sadleria" order="Polypodiales" pageId="2" pageNumber="95" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="genus">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="2" pageNumber="95">Sadleria</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
Kaulf., and 
<taxonomicName class="Equisetopsida" family="Woodsiaceae" genus="Diplazium" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Plantae" lsidName="Diplazium" order="Polypodiales" pageId="2" pageNumber="95" phylum="Magnolipsida" rank="genus">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="2" pageNumber="95">Diplazium</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
Sw. Flowering was observed from November to June and fruiting from January to August.
</paragraph>
